Task 7 - Basic visualization with R

1. Compare body heights of two species (magic_guys.csv)

library(ggplot2)

magic <- read.csv("~/Desktop/magic_guys.csv")

# a) histogram
hist(magic$length, breaks = 20, main = "Histogram of length", xlab = "length")

ggplot(magic, aes(x = length, fill = species)) +
  geom_histogram(alpha = 0.5, bins = 20) +
  theme_minimal()

# b) boxplot
boxplot(length ~ species, data = magic, main = "Boxplot of length")

ggplot(magic, aes(x = species, y = length, fill = species)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  theme_minimal()

# c) save plots 
ggsave("~/Desktop/heights_plot.png", width = 6, height = 4)
ggsave("~/Desktop/heights_plot.pdf", width = 6, height = 4)
if (requireNamespace("svglite", quietly = TRUE)) {
  ggsave("~/Desktop/heights_plot.svg", width = 6, height = 4)
}


# 2
expr <- read.table("~/Desktop/microarray_data.tab", header = TRUE, sep = "\t")

# a) rows  cols
dim(expr)
## [1]  553 1000
# b) missing values per gene
na_counts <- rowSums(is.na(expr))
hist(na_counts, main = "Missing values per gene", xlab = "NAs")

# c) more than 10%, 20%, 50%
n_samp <- ncol(expr)
sum(na_counts > 0.1 * n_samp)
## [1] 337
sum(na_counts > 0.2 * n_samp)
## [1] 236
sum(na_counts > 0.5 * n_samp)
## [1] 8
# d) impute missing with row mean
expr_imputed <- expr
row_means <- rowMeans(expr_imputed, na.rm = TRUE)
na_idx <- which(is.na(expr_imputed), arr.ind = TRUE)
expr_imputed[na_idx] <- row_means[na_idx[,1]]
